// Retrieve category list for a post in either HTML list or custom format.

<?php echo get_the_category_list(); ?> // By leaving the $separator value empty, it will generate an unordered list instead, complete with classes.

Result of above statement :

<ul class="post-categories">
    <li>
        <a href="http://w3villa.com/category/business" title="View all posts in Business" rel="category tag">Business</a>
    </li>
    <li>
        <a href="http://w3villa.com/category/development" title="View all posts in Development" rel="category tag">Deveopment</a>
    </li>
